This is Perl module AnyEvent::Gearman.

INSTALLATION

AnyEvent::Gearman installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is set up,
you should just be able to do

    % cpan AnyEvent::Gearman

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Make sure you have `Module::Install` and `Module::Install::AuthorTests` dependencies installed, as well as other prerequisites the build asks for.

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

AnyEvent::Gearman documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc AnyEvent::Gearman

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

Daisuke Murase
